aves.dpt.intf.production

Interface Factory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FactoryImpl

    public interface Factory
    Classes implementing this interface request the production of a List of AvesObjects that the AvesManager manages during a specific AvesManager.Phase.
    Author:
    svlieffe 2012/03/29

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  Factory.ProductionMode
      Defines the different modes of production that will themselves define the AvesObject.AvesObjectType requested by the Factory.

      java.util.List<AvesObject> listOfObjects()
      Return the list maintained by the Factory.

      Starts the production of requested objects and adds them to the list
      void setProductionMode(Factory.ProductionMode mode)
      sets the Factory.ProductionMode to the AvesManager.Phase determined by the AvesManager
      void setRequestedItem(java.lang.String item)
      Sets the name of the dataset of specific items requested by the user by selecting an object in the AvesViewer and send to the Factory through the AvesManager
